OL,3,CGisele Pelicot calmly faced the
OL,4,Cunimaginable in court for the final
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FHis verdict - the first to be read out
OL,8,F- came as no surprise. He had already
OL,9,Fadmitted his crimes but, under French
OL,10,Flaw, the accused must face trial and
OL,11,Ftheir guilt must be determined by a
OL,12,Fpanel of judges.
OL,14,FHe was asked to stand up to receive
OL,15,Fhis sentence of 20 years - which means
OL,16,Fhe is likely to spend the rest of his
OL,17,Flife in jail - and when he sat down
OL,18,Fagain he began to cry.
