OL,4,Cunimaginable in court for the final
OL,5,Ctime
OL,7,FHe was the first of 51 men to be
OL,8,Fconvicted and sentenced during a
OL,9,Fhearing that, remarkably, lasted for
OL,10,Fonly just over an hour.
OL,12,FHis co-defendants were described in
OL,13,Fcourt as 'Mr Everyman' - a 55-year-old
OL,14,Fnurse, a 27-year-old soldier, a 74-
OL,15,Fyear-old grandfather, a 56-year-old
OL,16,Fplumber with three kids.
OL,18,FThose that weren't already in custody
OL,19,Farrived, as usual, in hoods and face
OL,20,Fmasks. But this time they had also
OL,21,Fbeen advised to bring overnight bags.
